Nafamostat mesilate on the course of acute pancreatitis. Protective effect on peritoneal permeability and relation with supervening pulmonary distress. Three hundred sixty Sprague-Dawley rats were allocated into four groups, according to different content of a 24-h i.v. infusion performed 1 h after intrabiliary injection of enterokinase/sodium taurocholate to induce acute pancreatitis (AP): (1) Saline (2) 5 micrograms/kg/h nafamostat mesilate (FUT-175)